        <abstract> 
<p>Answers CD’s objections with botanical and geological arguments supporting the existence of an ancient post-Miocene land extending over what is now the Mediterranean and past the Azores in the Atlantic [EF’s "Atlantis" theory in "On the connexion between the distribution of the existing fauna and flora of the British Isles and the geological changes which have affected their area", <hi rend="italic">Mem. Geol. Surv. G. B.</hi> 1 (1846): 336–432].</p> 
        </abstract>
